Two people died in two separate accidents in Port Elizabeth on Friday night. Police spokesman Captain Johan Rheeder said at about 9:50pm a 25-year-old male driver collided into the barrier of the Commercial Road off-ramp on the N2. The man, who was alone in the vehicle, was driving a Renault and died at the scene. In the second incident a man, approximately in his 30s, was driving his scooter and collided with the barrier in the Over Valley section of Walmer at about 10:15pm. The mad died at the scene. “We have no further details at this stage. “The roads were wet and the two accidents happened within a short space of time of one another,” Rheeder said.